        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                <head>No. 330.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Anderson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-12-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 16, 1887</date>. (Received January 3,
                        1888.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 184.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to report that John A. Benson’s
                    brother who traveled with him under the assumed name of William B. Frank, and in
                    regard to whom you telegraphed me that there was no indictment against him, will
                    be released from prison in Copenhagen on Wednesday, December 21, and will sail
                    on that day in a Thingvalla steamer direct for New York.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">R. B. Anderson.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
